io.sphere.sdk.customobjects.queries

Interface CustomObjectByIdGet<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of the value of the custom object.
    All Superinterfaces:
    Get<CustomObject<T>>, SphereRequest<CustomObject<T>>

    public interface CustomObjectByIdGet<T>
extends Get<CustomObject<T>>
    SphereRequest to fetch one CustomObject by id. 
    withCustomObject(client(), existingCustomObject -> {
    final String id = existingCustomObject.getId();
    final CustomObjectByIdGet<Foo> fetch =
            CustomObjectByIdGet.of(id, Foo.class);
    final CustomObject<Foo> customObject = client().executeBlocking(fetch);
    assertThat(customObject).isEqualTo(existingCustomObject);
});

    See the test code.
